        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the syrup, cool completely",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the {{honey}}, {{caster-sugar}} (syrup portion), 150 ml water, and the juice of the {{lemon}} in a saucepan. Stir over medium heat until the sugar dissolves, then simmer for 10 minutes. Set aside to cool completely. See the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "hot pastry, cold syrup",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpa2cpjs0000ygv481iber10"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " rule: this must be cold before you pour it.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Layer the baklava",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 180°C fan. Mix the {{walnuts}}, {{cinnamon-ground}}, and {{caster-sugar}} (filling portion) together. Brush a 30 × 20 cm baking tin with melted {{unsalted-butter}}. Layer 6 sheets of {{filo-pastry}}, brushing each with butter. Spread half the walnut mixture evenly over the top. Layer 3 more filo sheets, each buttered. Spread the remaining walnut mixture. Finish with the remaining filo sheets, buttering each layer including the top. Cut through all layers into diamonds or squares before baking.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake 40 to 50 minutes, pour syrup",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 40 to 50 minutes until deep golden brown. Remove from the oven and immediately pour the cold syrup evenly over the hot baklava. Leave to cool completely at room temperature for at least 2 hours before serving, retracing the cuts as needed.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
